              >
                <div class="faq-tile">
                  <div
                    class="faq-block"
                    style="  border-top: 1px dashed white;"
                  >
                    <!-- Q1 -->
                    <div
                      class="expandable-single"
                      style="  border-top: 1px dashed white;"
                    >
                      <div class="expandable-top">
                        <div class="text-h6">What is a telecoil?</div>
                        <div class="faq-animated-box">
                          <div class="faq-horizontal-light"></div>
                          <div class="faq-vertical-light"></div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="expandable-bottom">
                        <p class="faq-paragraph">
                          A telecoil (or “T-coil”) is a tiny copper loop built
                          into many hearing aids and all cochlear implants. When
                          you switch to the “T” program, the device stops using
                          its microphone and instead receives the magnetic
                          signal broadcast by an assistive-listening system—most
                          often a hearing loop, FM/RF, or infrared feed—and
                          converts that signal directly into clear,
                          high-fidelity audio.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div
                      class="expandable-single"
                      style="  border-top: 1px dashed white;"
                    >
                      <div class="expandable-top">
                        <div class="text-h6">How do I activate a Telecoil?</div>
                        <div class="faq-animated-box">
                          <div
                            class="faq-horizontal-light"
                            style="background-color: ;"
                          >
                          </div>
                          <div
                            class="faq-vertical-light"
                            style="background-color: ;"
                          >
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="expandable-bottom">
                        <p class="faq-paragraph">
                          Switch your hearing aid to the T program when you’re
                          in a looped area. This turns off the microphone and
                          lets your aid pick up the loop’s magnetic signal for
                          clearer sound. Switch back to normal to hear as usual.<br
                          /><br />If you need to hear both loop audio and
                          ambient sound, e.g., conversation with someone beside
                          you—choose the “MT” or “Mic+T” program if your aid
                          offers it.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div
                      class="expandable-single"
                      style="  border-top: 1px dashed white;"
                    >
                      <div class="expandable-top">
                        <div class="text-h6">
                          Why should a hearing aid include a telecoil?
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-animated-box">
                          <div class="faq-horizontal-light"></div>
                          <div class="faq-vertical-light"></div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="expandable-bottom">
                        <p class="faq-paragraph">
                          A telecoil effectively doubles the versatility of your
                          hearing device. It gives you instant, cable-free
                          access to loop-equipped theatres, transport hubs,
                          houses of worship, council chambers, museum tours, and
                          even in-home TV loops. The result is markedly clearer
                          speech with minimal background noise and no extra
                          hardware to carry.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Q3 -->
                    <div
                      class="expandable-single"
                      style="  border-top: 1px dashed white;"
                    >
                      <div class="expandable-top">
                        <div class="text-h6">Isn’t Bluetooth sufficient?</div>
                        <div class="faq-animated-box">
                          <div class="faq-horizontal-light"></div>
                          <div class="faq-vertical-light"></div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="expandable-bottom">
                        <p class="faq-paragraph">
                          Bluetooth is ideal for short-range links to a phone or
                          tablet, but it is not the global standard for
                          large-area assistive listening and often requires
                          brand-specific accessories. A telecoil is universal:
                          walk into any looped venue, flip to “T,” and you are
                          connected.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Q4 -->
                    <div
                      class="expandable-single"
                      style="  border-top: 1px dashed white;"
                    >
                      <div class="expandable-top">
                        <div class="text-h6">
                          How can I confirm whether my current aids have an
                          active telecoil?
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-animated-box">
                          <div class="faq-horizontal-light"></div>
                          <div class="faq-vertical-light"></div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="expandable-bottom">
                        <p class="faq-paragraph">
                          Check with your audiologist or your user manual. Many
                          models highlight the feature with a “T” in the product
                          name (e.g.,
                          <em>miniRITE T</em>) or list “telecoil” in the
                          specifications, but the program may still need to be
                          enabled in the clinic.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Q5 -->
                    <div
                      class="expandable-single"
                      style="  border-top: 1px dashed white;"
                    >
                      <div class="expandable-top">
                        <div class="text-h6">
                          What should I specify when purchasing new aids?
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-animated-box">
                          <div class="faq-horizontal-light"></div>
                          <div class="faq-vertical-light"></div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="expandable-bottom">
                        <p class="faq-paragraph">
                          Ask for <strong>access-ready</strong> instruments that
                          include a Built-in telecoil. Ideally, a single button or
                          app should let you switch between microphone, telecoil,
                          and Auracast modes without neck-loops or dongles.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
